Awka â€“ The Commissioner of Police, Anambra State Command, CP Echeng Echeng has expressed profound gratitude to the Inspector General of Police, IGP Alkali Baba Usman and his management team for the approval and delivery of three operational vehicles to Anambra State Police Command. The press statement released by the Police Public Relations Officer in the state command DSP Ikenga Tochukwu revealed that on 13th January,2022 at the Force Headquarters Abuja, operational vehicles and gadgets were donated to the Nigeria Police Force by His Excellency, the President and Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces, Federal Republic of Nigeria, President Muhammadu Buhari through the Nigeria Police Trust Fund. The commissioner of police CP Echeng Eworo Echeng said that the gesture will boost the morale of the Anambra State Police Command, enhance public safety, peace as well as improve their operational performance in the state.